s%20use%20cutting-edge%20technology%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdronelife.com%2F2023%2F06%2F07%2Fintelligent-drone-swarms-could-mimic-bird-flocks-new-research-from-university-of-houston%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20derived%20from%20studying%20bird%20flocks%20and%20fish%20shoals%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20coordinate%20their%20movements%20across%20a%20potentially%20vast%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20could%20enable%20militaries%20not%20just%20to%20surveil%20the%20enemy%20but%20be%20used%20as%20weapons%20to%20launch%20huge%20coordinated%20bombing%20attacks.%20But%20work%20remains%20to%20be%20done%20on%20identifying%20their%20most%20effective%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDrone%20swarms%20are%20useful%20for%20a%20broad%20range%20of%20military%20operations%20from%20finding%20and%20destroying%20submarines%20to%20blowing%20up%20tanks%20and%20cleaning%20out%20enemy%20air%20defenses%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Zak%20Kallenborn%2C%20an%20analyst%20who%20specializes%20in%20drones%20and%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKellenborn%20is%20the%20top%20researcher%20at%20Looking%20Glass%20USA%2C%20a%20counter-drone%20consultancy%2C%20and%20is%20also%20affiliated%20with%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BExactly%20which%20mission%20drone%20swarms%20are%20best%20suited%20to%20is%20unclear%2C%20but%20their%20potential%20is%20huge%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20challenge%20is%20separating%20where%20drone%20swarms%20really%20matter%20from%20where%20they're%20mostly%20cool%20sci-fi%20stuff.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20threat%20they%20pose%20to%20militaries%20is%20so%20intense%20that%20military%20experts%20are%20already%20working%20on%20ways%20to%20counter%20their%20capabilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUkraine%20supercharged%20drone%20combat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20has%20transformed%20the%20way%20drones%20are%20being%20used%20in%20war.%20In%20the%20conflict%2C%20cheap%2C%20airborne%20drones%20have%20been%20deployed%20for%20tasks%20from%20surveillance%20to%20bombings%20and%20even%20directing%20the%20surrender%20of%20enemy%20soldiers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-sea-drone-pilot-relives-hitting-russia-ship-new-tech-2023-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproved%20their%20worth%20at%20sea%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20on%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20military%20planners%20are%20studying%20the%20conflict%20for%20clues%20about%20how%20to%20deploy%20drones%20for%20the%20wars%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEverybody%20in%20the%20Western%20military%20establishments%20is%20eagerly%20trying%20to%20understand%20and%20digest%20insights%20coming%20out%20of%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20David%20Ochmanek%2C%20an%20analyst%20at%20the%20RAND%20Corporation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20sounds%20awful%20this%20way%2C%20but%20we%20don't%20have%20very%20many%20opportunities%20to%20learn%20from%20real-world%2C%20large-scale%20combat%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20recently%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2016%2F05%2Fwhy-concerns-over-drone-proliferation-are-overblown%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esome%20military%20experts%20argued%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20drones%20were%20too%20easy%20to%20shoot%20down%2C%20and%20would%20likely%20only%20feature%20in%20wars%20between%20poorer%20nations%20without%20the%20resources%20to%20counter%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20lesson%20from%20Ukraine%2C%20Ochmanek%20believes%2C%20is%20that%20drones%20will%20feature%20in%20conflicts%20involving%20even%20the%20most%20powerful%20nations%20%E2%80%94%20on%20an%20even%20larger%20scale%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20deploying%20individual%20drones%2C%20each%20of%20which%20is%20controlled%20by%20a%20single%20human%20operator%2C%20as%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20US%20could%20field%20massive%20swarms%20of%20drones%20operating%20autonomously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20a%20conflict%20with%20a%20major%20power%2C%20such%20as%20China%2C%20they%20could%20help%20the%20US%20secure%20a%20key%20advantage%2C%20said%20Ochmanek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20have%20to%20find%20a%20way%20in%20the%20opening%20hours%20of%20a%20conflict%20with%20China%2C%20not%20weeks%20or%20days%2C%20but%20hours%2C%20to%20characterize%20what's%20happening%20in%20that%20battlespace%2C%20identify%20the%20targets%20of%20greatest%20interest%2C%20track%20those%20targets%2C%20and%20engage%20them%20to%20destroy%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ochmanek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%20seeks%20to%20neutralize%20US%20war%20plans%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20years%2C%20a%20problem%20has%20bedeviled%20US%20military%20planners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBack%20in%20the%201990s%20and%20early%202000s%2C%20the%20US%20developed%20tactics%20to%20rapidly%20wipe%20out%20an%20enemy's%20command%20systems%20and%20air%20defenses%20using%20a%20combination%20of%20satellite%20surveillance%20and%20precision-guided%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tactics%20were%20deployed%20to%20devastating%20effect%20by%20the%20US%20against%20Iraq%20in%20both%201991%20and%202003.%20The%20US%20obliterated%20Iraqi%20air%20defenses%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20hours%2C%20giving%20it%20control%20of%20the%20battlefield%20and%20air%20space.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%2C%20which%20was%20rapidly%20gaining%20economic%20and%20military%20might%2C%20was%20watching%2C%20and%20urgently%20upgraded%20its%20military%20and%20refined%20its%20tactics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20found%20ways%20to%20move%20or%20conceal%20its%20air%20defense%20systems%20and%20other%20potential%20targets%2C%20making%20them%20difficult%20for%20the%20US%20to%20locate%20and%20potentially%20destroy%2C%20said%20Ochmanek.%20It%20also%20developed%20technology%20to%20shield%20the%20location%20of%20weapons%20and%20other%20key%20sites%20from%20satellites%20by%20%26quot%3Bdazzling%26quot%3B%20them%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Fsearch%3Fq%3Dcghina%2Bstaellite%2Bdazzling%26oq%3Dcghina%2Bstaellite%2Bdazzling%2B%26gs_lcrp%3DEgZjaHJvbWUyBggAEEUYOTIJCAEQIRgKGKABMgkIAhAhGAoYoAEyCQgDECEYChigATIJCAQQIRgKGKAB0gEINDI0NmowajeoAgCwAgA%26sourceid%3Dchrome%26ie%3DUTF-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esay%20US%20military%20analysts.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20was%20sent%20back%20to%20the%20drawing%20board%2C%20seeking%20to%20regain%20its%20advantage.%20And%20that%2C%20says%20Ochmanek%2C%20is%20where%20drones%20could%20come%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20drone%20swarm%20offers%20key%20advantages%20in%20identifying%20targets%20in%20the%20early%20hours%20of%20a%20conflict.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20deployed%20in%20such%20vast%20numbers%20that%20they%20overwhelm%20air%20defense%20systems.%20Once%20there%2C%20they%20can%20relay%20live%20data%20to%20human%20operators%20who%20would%20use%20it%20to%20guide%20precision%20missile%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20though%20the%20US%20uses%20drones%20far%20more%20expensive%20than%20the%20ones%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20they%20are%20still%20very%20cheap%20compared%20to%20a%20lot%20of%20military%20gear%2C%20like%20fighter%20jets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20drone%20swarm%20looks%20to%20us%20like%20a%20robust%20way%20to%20do%20what%20we%20need%20to%20do%20to%20gain%20the%20information%20we%20need%20so%20that%20the%20limited%20lethality%20we%20can%20generate%20in%20those%20opening%20hours%20and%20days%20of%20war%20is%20applied%20effectively%20and%20efficiently%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ochmanek.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EKiller%20robots%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20critics%20are%20warning%20that%20the%20drone%20swarms%20could%20usher%20in%20a%20terrifying%20future%20.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20drone%20swarm%20plans%20envisaged%20by%20military%20experts%2C%20the%20machines%20rely%20on%20humans%20as%20decision-makers%20before%20any%20actual%20attacks%20are%20made.%20The%20drones%20only%20give%20information.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20not%20be%20a%20big%20technological%20leap%20to%20give%20the%20drones%20power%20to%20make%20those%20decisions%20themselves%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20prospect%20of%20crossing%20that%20moral%20boundary%20is%20raising%20the%20alarm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20United%20Nations%20last%20year%2C%20several%20countries%20called%20for%20restrictions%20on%20the%20development%20and%20use%20of%20autonomous%20drones%20capable%20of%20making%20life-and-death%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20China%20both%20opposed%20that%20plan%2C%20arguing%20that%20current%20restrictions%20on%20using%20any%20weapons%20to%20indiscriminately%20target%20civilians%20were%20sufficient%20to%20preclude%20a%20future%20of%20killer%20robots.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKallenborn%2C%20the%20analyst%2C%20does%20support%20more%20explicit%20restrictions%2C%20arguing%20that%20drone%20swarms%20could%20be%20considered%20weapons%20of%20mass%20destruction%20and%20therefore%20need%20to%20be%20banned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20key%20problem%2C%20he%20said%2C%20is%20that%20the%20technology%20can%20make%20mistakes.%20And%20because%20the%20drones%20communicate%20with%20each%20other%2C%20one%20mistake%20could%20rapidly%20spread%20and%20multiply.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAutonomous%2C%20armed%20drone%20swarms%20should%20have%20restrictions%20on%20their%20use%2C%20especially%20drone%20swarms%20targeting%20humans.%20We%20know%20that%20autonomous%20weapons%20are%20prone%20to%20mistakes%3B%20a%20drone%20swarm%20scales%20that%20risk%20a%20thousandfold%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Kallenborn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20sensor%20drone%20might%20misidentify%20a%20school%20bus%20as%20a%20tank%2C%20and%20tell%2010%20other%20drones%20to%20blow%20it%20up%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOchmanek%20stressed%20that%20targeting%20decisions%20for%20drone%20swarms%20should%20still%20be%20made%20by%20humans%2C%20with%20AI%20only%20synthesizing%20the%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20long%20as%20there's%20a%20communication%20link%20between%20the%20mesh%20and%20human%20operators%20in%20the%20rear%2C%20humans%20will%20be%20evaluating%20for%20themselves%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20the%20mesh%20is%20making%20accurate%20assessments%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECountering%20the%20swarms%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20well%20as%20developing%20plans%20to%20deploy%20drone%20swarms%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.defenseone.com%2Fbusiness%2F2023%2F07%2Fdefense-startups-team-defeat-swarm-drones%2F388909%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefense%20companies%20are%20working%20on%20a%20playbook%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20countering%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EResearch%20is%20underway%20on%20how%20to%20take%20them%20out%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbritain-shows-off-dragonfire-laser-weapon-take-out-drones-cheap-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eusing%20lasers%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.scientificamerican.com%2Farticle%2Fnew-microwave-weapons-could-defend-against-swarms-of-combat-drones%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emicrowaves%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20both%20approaches%20have%20drawbacks%20of%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20possibility%2C%20said%20Ochmanek%2C%20is%20that%20drone%20swarms%20could%20be%20programmed%20to%20target%20other%20drone%20swarms.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20far%2C%20he%20added%2C%20no%20magic%20bullet%20had%20been%20found%20to%20counter%20the%20swarms.%20And%20despite%20fears%20about%20their%20autonomy%2C%20they%20seem%20poised%20to%20play%20a%20central%20role%20in%20the%20wars%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrone-swarms-how-emerging-tech-could-transform-future-wars-2024-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711959421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.