ams%20was%20stuck%20with%20an%20eye-watering%20medical%20bill%20of%20nearly%20%245%2C000%20after%20being%20treated%20for%20a%20simple%20case%20of%20dehydration%20following%20an%20overnight%20stay%20at%20an%20Arizona%20hospital%20last%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20he's%20calling%20for%20reforms%20to%20the%20country's%20market-based%20health%20care%20system%2C%20including%20greater%20transparency%20around%20costs%20and%20an%20independent%20arbitration%20process%20--%20while%20using%20his%20bully%20pulpit%20to%20speak%20out%20for%20the%20100%20million%20Americans%20saddled%20with%20medical%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20the%20rate%20of%20uninsured%20Americans%20has%20been%20declining%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20The%20Commonwealth%20Fund%20estimates%20that%2043%20percent%20of%20working-age%20adults%20are%20%26quot%3Bunderinsured%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20limits%20their%20access%20to%20care%20and%20leaves%20many%20just%20one%20major%20catastrophe%20away%20from%20financial%20ruin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20out%20at%20the%20Society%20of%20Critical%20Care%20Medicine%20meeting%20in%20Phoenix%2C%20Arizona%2C%20and%20like%20literally%20thousands%20of%20tourists%20visiting%20that%20area%2C%20I%20decided%20that%20I%20would%20go%20and%20hike%20up%20Camelback%20Mountain%2C%26quot%3B%20the%2049-year-old%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20along%20a%20bottle%20of%20water%2C%20more%20than%20enough%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20for%20a%2060%20degree%20Fahrenheit%20(16%20degree%20Celsius)%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20by%20the%20time%20he%20was%20heading%20out%20for%20dinner%20he%20started%20feeling%20dizzy%20and%20lightheaded%20--%20and%20his%20fellow%20doctors%20advised%20him%20it%20was%20best%20to%20get%20it%20checked%20out%2C%20especially%20as%20a%20middle-aged%20Black%20man%20at%20higher%20risk%20of%20cardiovascular%20complications.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20called%20an%20ambulance%20because%20I%20was%20out%20of%20town.%20I%20got%20IV%20fluids%20on%20the%20way.%20And%20by%20the%20time%20I%20got%20there%2C%20it%20was%20pretty%20clear%20that%20it%20was%20dehydration%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20in%20Indiana%2C%20where%20he%20now%20works%20at%20Purdue%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20took%20medics'%20advice%20and%20stayed%20overnight%2C%20and%20two%20months%20later%20received%20a%20bill%20for%20%244%2C800.%20Threats%20of%20being%20sent%20to%20collections%20agencies%20soon%20followed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdams%20said%20he%20was%20well%20aware%20his%20situation%20was%20all%20too%20common%20in%20a%20country%20where%20nearly%2066%20percent%20of%20all%20bankruptcies%20are%20directly%20tied%20to%20medical%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20as%20a%20Black%20physician%20who%20walked%20a%20tightrope%20to%20advocate%20for%20racial%20justice%20in%20health%20care%20--%20both%20as%20Donald%20Trump's%20surgeon%20general%2C%20and%20before%20that%20as%20head%20of%20Indiana's%20health%20department%20under%20Mike%20Pence%20--%20Adams%20said%20he%20could%20be%20a%20champion%20for%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20complaint%20isn't%20about%20me%20personally%2C%20because%20I%20will%20be%20okay%20--%20but%20I%20do%20have%20a%20voice%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20insisted.%20Since%20the%20incident%2C%20he%20has%20kept%20busy%20posting%20to%20his%20nearly%2090%2C000%20X%20followers%20about%20other%20cases%2C%20such%20as%20a%20mother%20of%20premature%20quadruplets%20handed%20a%20bill%20of%20%244%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3EMarket%20reforms%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20progressives%20like%20Vermont%20Senator%20Bernie%20Sanders%20have%20proposed%20eliminating%20private%20health%20insurance%20altogether%2C%20Adams%20says%20that's%20not%20realistic%20given%20that%20too%20many%20players%20profit%20from%20the%20status%20quo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERather%2C%20he%20advocates%20for%20a%20set%20of%20reforms%20that%20work%20to%20regulate%20the%20free%20market%2C%20just%20as%20the%20Affordable%20Care%20Act%2C%20better%20known%20as%20Obamacare%2C%20did%20in%20the%202010s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20more%20transparency%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20can't%20have%20a%20market%20without%20transparency%20and%20without%20accountability%20--%20and%20right%20now%2C%20if%20I%20went%20to%20a%20car%20dealer%2C%20they%20would%20have%20to%20tell%20me%20how%20much%20the%20car%20costs.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20he%20says%2C%20there%20needs%20to%20be%20an%20arbitration%20process%20where%20the%20hospital%20that%20provided%20the%20care%20--%20the%20Mayo%20Clinic%20in%20his%20particular%20case%20--%20aren't%20given%20full%20reign%20and%20patients%20have%20no%20recourse%20to%20contest%20their%20mega%20bills.%20Mayo%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20requested%20comment%20to%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20while%20Obamacare%20helped%20bring%20coverage%20to%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20Americans%2C%20it%20partly%20did%20so%20by%20incentivizing%20employers%20to%20provide%20workers%20with%20plans%20that%20cost%20them%20less%20--%20but%20also%20pay%20out%20much%20less%2C%20said%20Adams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20these%20plans%20--%20which%20includes%20Adams%20himself%20--%20can%20make%20contributions%20to%20tax-free%20spending%20accounts%20in%20order%20to%20offset%20some%20of%20their%20risk.%20But%20if%20a%20health%20incident%20occurs%20early%20on%20in%20the%20year%2C%20they%20may%20not%20have%20enough%20stashed%20away%20--%20and%20in%20such%20cases%2C%20legislation%20should%20be%20passed%20requiring%20insurers%20foot%20a%20larger%20portion%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Adams%2C%20who%20grew%20up%20with%20severe%20asthma%20and%20saw%20repeated%20trips%20to%20the%20hospital%20as%20a%20child%20because%20his%20parents%20couldn't%20afford%20his%20medications%2C%20the%20policies%20he's%20advocated%20for%20during%20his%20career%20have%20always%20been%20personal%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere's%20a%20lot%20of%20trade-offs%20that%20we%20have%20here%2C%26quot%3