nd.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20why%20do%20brands%20love%20jumping%20on%20the%20April%20Fools%20bandwagon%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20long%20history%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20origins%20of%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20remain%20a%20mystery%2C%20there%20are%20some%20theories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20suggest%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20can%20be%20traced%20back%20to%20classical%20Roman%20times%2C%20quite%20possibly%20an%20equinox%20celebration%2C%20recognising%20the%20end%20of%20the%20European%20winter%20and%20the%20coming%20of%20spring.%20Similarly%20to%20the%20Roman%20festival%20of%20Hilaria%2C%20celebrated%20in%20late%20March%20and%20marked%20with%20fun%2C%20gaiety%20and%20the%20wearing%20of%20disguises.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20alternative%20theory%20offers%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20originated%20in%2016th%20century%20France%2C%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20New%20Year%20was%20observed%20on%20April%201%2C%20before%20the%20introduction%20of%20the%20Gregorian%20Calendar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fapril-fools-day-2024-know-about-the-day-its-history-and-origin-5349512%5C%22%3EApril%20Fools'%20Day%202024%3A%20Know%20About%20The%20Day%2C%20Its%20History%20And%20Origin%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20France%2C%20the%20first%20reference%20to%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Epoisson%20d'avril%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9D%20(%E2%80%9CApril%20fish%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20name%20for%20a%20person%20tricked%20on%20April%20Fools'%20Day)%20appeared%20in%20poem%20by%20Eloy%20D'Amerval%20in%201508.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201686%2C%20English%20antiquarian%20John%20Aubrey%20first%20mentioned%20%E2%80%9CFooles%20Holy%20Day%E2%80%9D%2C%20observed%20on%20April%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPossibly%2C%20the%20earliest%20April%20Fools%20advert%20appeared%20in%20Britain%20on%20April%201%201698%2C%20inviting%20gullible%20people%20to%20bring%20a%20friend%20to%20the%20Tower%20of%20London%20to%20%E2%80%9Csee%20the%20washing%20of%20the%20Lions%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganisations%20began%20to%20truly%20leverage%20the%20day%20from%20the%201950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%201955%2C%20Popular%20Electronics%20magazine%20ran%20an%20article%20about%20%E2%80%9Ccontra-polar%20energy%E2%80%9D.%20The%20hoax%20article%20claimed%20the%20government%20had%20lifted%20restrictions%20on%20secret%20second%20world%20war%20electronics%20developments%2C%20which%20enabled%20the%20magazine%20to%20finally%20report%20on%20a%20new%20%E2%80%9Cnegative%20energy%E2%80%9D%20innovation%20that%20would%20cause%20electrical%20devices%20to%20produce%20the%20opposite%20effect%20of%20what%20they%20normally%20would%20do.%20For%20instance%2C%20a%20table%20lamp%20that%20generates%20%E2%80%9Cdarkness%E2%80%9D%20rather%20than%20%E2%80%9Clight%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20an%20electric%20hotplate%20that%20freezes%20water%2C%20rather%20than%20boils%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20famously%2C%20the%20BBC%20current%20affairs%20programme%20Panorama%20reported%20on%20a%20%E2%80%9Cspaghetti%20tree%E2%80%9D%20on%20April%20Fools'%20Day%201957.%20The%20man%20largely%20responsible%20for%20the%20hoax%20was%20Austrian-born%20Panorama%20cameraman%20Charles%20de%20Jaeger%2C%20who%20liked%20to%20play%20practical%20jokes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERead%20%7C%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fapril-fools-day-2023-history-and-origin-3908423%5C%22%3EApril%20Fools'%20Day%3A%20All%20You%20Need%20To%20Know%20About%20Its%20History%20And%20Origin%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20segment%20showed%20farmers%20apparently%20picking%20spaghetti%20from%20trees%20and%20laying%20the%20strands%20out%20to%20dry.%20BBC%20reporter%20Richard%20Dimbleby%20was%20in%20on%20the%20joke%20and%20his%20authority%20lent%20credence%20to%20the%20ruse%20%E2%80%93%20reportedly%2C%20hundreds%20called%20the%20BBC%20asking%20where%20they%20could%20buy%20their%20own%20spaghetti%20trees.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20a%20myriad%20of%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20Pranks%20have%20been%20played%20by%20global%20corporations%20and%20brands%20around%20the%20world%2C%20using%20the%20start%20of%20April%20to%20embrace%20%E2%80%9Cprankvertising%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20power%20of%20prankvertising%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contemporary%20marketing%2C%20prankvertising%20%E2%80%93%20a%20mash-up%20of%20the%20words%20%E2%80%9Cprank%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cadvertising%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20used%20for%20online%20branding%20purposes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20%E2%80%9Cprofessionally%20developed%E2%80%9D%20pranks%20are%20created%20by%20advertising%20agencies%2C%20often%20planned%20well%20ahead%20of%20execution%20and%20with%20anticipated%20results.%20In%20digital%20media%2C%20prankvertising%20has%20become%20a%20tactic%20for%20individuals'%20attention%20in%20a%20highly%20crowded%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20has%20found%20a%20carefully%20crafted%20%E2%80%9Cprankvertisement%E2%80%9D%20can%20increase%20an%20individual's%20perception%20of%20brand%20%E2%80%9Cfriendliness%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Clove%E2%80%9D%2C%20generate%20greater%20engagement%20and%20memorability%2C%20leading%20to%20a%20stronger%20willingness%20to%20buy%20%E2%80%93%20even%20when%20the%20product%20or%20announcement%20they%20are%20advertising%20is%20fake.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20humour%20works%20to%20humanise%20brands%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHumour%2C%20jokes%20and%20pranks%20are%20more%20greatly%20associated%20with%20humans%2C%20rather%20than%20organisations%20or%20brands.%20We%20all%20have%20a%20member%20of%20the%20family%20or%20a%20friend%20who%20we%20consider%20a%20lot%20of%20fun%20or%20a%20bit%20of%20a%20prankster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndividuals%20generally%20desire%20partners%20who%20have%20a%20%E2%80%9Cgood%20sense%20of%20humour%E2%80%9D.%20In%20a%20workplace%2C%20humour%20between%20colleagues%20can%20build%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOrganisations%20and%20brands%20want%20to%20attain%20these%20same%20outcomes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdvertising%20or%20promoting%20firm-initiated%20amusing%20media%20are%20more%20likely%20than%20non-humourous%20posts%20to%20encourage%20positive%20comments%2C%20likes%20and%20re-posts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncongruity%20theory%20says%20humour%20arises%20when%20two%20contrasting%20ideas%20are%20mingled.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20CSIRO%2C%20police%20forces%20and%20emergency%20services%20are%20important%2C%20credible%20and%20%E2%80%9Cserious%E2%80%9D%20organisations%20we%20normally%20don't%20associate%20with%20pranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20they%20participate%20in%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20events%20they%20generate%20greater%20levels%20of%20engagement%2C%20humour%20and%20fun%2C%20because%20we%20don't%20associate%20these%20organisations%20with%20pranks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20engaging%20in%20April%20Fools'%20Day%20pranks%2C%20organisations%20and%20brands%20can%20build%20relationships%20and%20connect%20in%20the%20same%20way%20humans%20do%2C%20by%20creating%20positive%20emotions%20though%20entertaining%20(hopefully%20viral)%20campaigns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20today%2C%20when%20you%20see%20stories%20about%20%E2%80%9Ciced%20coffee-inspired%20deodorant%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9CNutella-flavoured%20Tic%20Tacs%E2%80%9D%2C%20take%20a%20moment%20to%20think%20if%20you've%20just%20been%20sucked%20into%20prankvertising.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E(Author%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fgary-mortimer-1322%5C%22%3EGary%20Mortimer%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Marketing%20and%20Consumer%20Behaviour%2C%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fqueensland-university-of-technology-847%5C%22%3EQueensland%20University%20of%20Technology%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%2