%3EBeing%20second%20in%20line%20for%20leadership%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20country%20in%20the%20world%20is%20not%20an%20easy%20job.%20But%20for%20Mike%20Pence%2C%20vice%20president%20under%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20things%20were%20even%20harder%20than%20usual.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20insurrectionists%20descended%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20on%20January%206%2C%202021%2C%20they%20had%20a%20specific%20target%20in%20mind%20%E2%80%93%20the%20outgoing%20vice%20president.%20They%20built%20a%20wooden%20gallows%2C%20and%20called%20out%20for%20him%20by%20name%3A%20%E2%80%9CHang%20Mike%20Pence!%20Hang%20Mike%20Pence!%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20extensive%20congressional%20hearings%20into%20the%20insurrection%20later%20documented%2C%20the%20threats%20were%20not%20hollow.%20One%20informant%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fnews%2Fletter-from-bidens-washington%2Fwhat-we-learned-about-trump-pence-and-the-january-6th-mob%5C%22%3Etold%20FBI%20investigators%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Cif%20given%20the%20chance%E2%80%9D%2C%20certain%20far-right%20insurrectionists%20would%20have%20tried%20to%20kill%20him.%20Pence%20escaped%20with%20his%20life%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Fpolitics%2Fpence-rioters-capitol-attack%2F2021%2F01%2F15%2Fab62e434-567c-11eb-a08b-f1381ef3d207_story.html%5C%22%3Eonly%20just%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20insurrectionists%2C%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lawfaremedia.org%2Fcurrent-projects%2Fthe-trump-trials%2Ftrump-prosecuted-in-the-district-of-columbia%5C%22%3Efederal%20investigation%3C%2Fa%3E%20alleges%2C%20were%20drawn%20to%20the%20Capitol%20by%20Trump%2C%20who%20had%20just%20lost%20the%202020%20election%20to%20Joe%20Biden.%20They%20were%20after%20Trump's%20VP%20because%2C%20as%20one%20later%20claimed%2C%20he%20had%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fnews%2Fletter-from-bidens-washington%2Fwhat-we-learned-about-trump-pence-and-the-january-6th-mob%5C%22%3Ebetrayed%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20Trump%20by%20not%20refusing%20to%20certify%20the%20election%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20of%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20is%20not%20a%20normal%20one%20at%20the%20best%20of%20times.%20The%20person%20chosen%20to%20run%20alongside%20Trump%20in%20this%20year's%20election%20will%20no%20doubt%20be%20keeping%20Pence's%20experience%20in%20mind.%20It%20will%20likely%20be%20someone%20who%20can%20convincingly%20pledge%20undying%20loyalty%20to%20Trump.%20The%20former%20president%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20supporters%20%E2%80%93%20will%20expect%20nothing%20less.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeculation%20over%20who%20that%20person%20might%20be%20is%20heating%20up%2C%20and%20Trump%2C%20as%20usual%2C%20is%20relishing%20drawing%20out%20the%20process%20in%20order%20to%20gain%20as%20much%20attention%20as%20possible.%20So%2C%20who%20%E2%80%93%20and%20how%20%E2%80%93%20will%20he%20choose%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaking%20race%20a%20priority%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20vice%20presidential%20candidate%20is%20usually%20chosen%20based%20on%20a%20political%20calculation.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20running%20mate%20can%20be%20seen%20to%20offset%20a%20presidential%20nominee's%20weaknesses%20(be%20they%20real%20or%20perceived).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20relatively%20young%20northerner%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%2C%20for%20example%2C%20chose%20the%20much%20more%20politically%20experienced%20southerner%2C%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson.%20Barack%20Obama%2C%20running%20to%20be%20the%20first%20Black%20president%2C%20similarly%20chose%20the%20older%20and%20more%20experienced%20%E2%80%93%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnymag.com%2Fintelligencer%2F2019%2F06%2Fwhy-did-obama-pick-biden-as-his-veep-in-the-first-place.html%5C%22%3Ereassuringly%20white%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20first%20run%2C%20Trump%20settled%20on%20Pence%20to%20offset%20his%20perceived%20weakness%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vox.com%2F2017%2F6%2F24%2F15865370%2Fmike-pence-focus-on-family-evangelicals%5C%22%3Eevangelical%20voters%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20a%20critical%20mobilising%20base%20to%20any%20Republican%20candidate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EViewed%20through%20this%20lens%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftrump-seeking-advice-friends-allies-running-mate-pick-2024-01-25%2F%5C%22%3Ecommonly%20accepted%20wisdom%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20that%20Trump%20has%20both%20a%20race%20and%20a%20woman%20problem%2C%20and%20that%20he%20should%20choose%20a%20VP%20candidate%20who%20can%20address%20at%20least%20one%20of%20those%20concerns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20category%2C%20the%20leading%20candidates%20appear%20to%20be%20two%20men%20who%20ran%20against%20Trump%20for%20this%20year's%20nomination%20%E2%80%93%20Tim%20Scott%20and%20Vivek%20Ramaswamy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EScott%20%E2%80%93%20a%20South%20Carolinian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fopinion%2Farticles%2F2024-03-05%2Ftim-scott-checks-the-boxes-for-trump-vp%5C%22%3Ethat%20Bloomberg%20has%3C%2Fa%3E%20dubbed%20%E2%80%9CTrump's%20New%20Black%20Best%20Friend%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20is%20the%20only%20Black%20Republican%20in%20the%20Senate.%20He%20has%20certainly%20indicated%20he%20is%20keen%20for%20the%20job%2C%20professing%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-us-canada-68077091%5C%22%3Elove%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Trump%20and%20recently%20announcing%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.washingtonpost.com%2Felections%2F2024%2F01%2F21%2Ftim-scott-engaged-vp-trump%2F%5C%22%3Eengagement%3C%2Fa%3E%20(being%20single%20is%20generally%20regarded%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vanityfair.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F09%2Ftim-scott-claims-republican-hopefuls-feasting-on-his-bachelorhood%5C%22%3Ea%20political%20liability%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20Republican%20campaign%20for%20the%20presidential%20nomination%2C%20Ramaswamy%20had%20presented%20himself%20as%20the%20newer%2C%20shinier%20Trump.%20In%20one%20memorable%20moment%20in%20the%20debates%2C%20he%20was%20first%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F08%2F24%2Fus%2Fpolitics%2Ftrump-convicted-republican-debate-hands.html%5C%22%3Eraise%20his%20hand%3C%2Fa%3E%20when%20the%20candidates%20were%20asked%20who%20would%20still%20support%20Trump%20if%20he%20is%20convicted%20of%20a%20crime.%20Ramaswamy%20also%20quickly%20endorsed%20Trump%20when%20he%20dropped%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20would%20no%20doubt%20be%20pleased%20with%20such%20public%20professions%20of%20loyalty.%20But%20there%20is%20no%20indication%20Trump%20considers%20race%20to%20be%20a%20problem%20for%20his%20candidacy%20%E2%80%93%20in%20fact%2C%20quite%20the%20opposite.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20has%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fus-news%2F2024%2Fmar%2F05%2Fdonald-trump-migrants-hannibal-lecter%5C%22%3Eleaning%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20increasingly%20extreme%20racist%20rhetoric.%20If%20he%20thought%20race%20mattered%20to%20his%20chances%2C%20he%20would%20likely%20be%20behaving%20differently.%20Trump's%20political%20rise%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fdonald-trump-faces-half-a-billion-dollars-of-debt-and-several-court-cases-but-that-may-not-stop-him-from-becoming-president-again-223813%5C%22%3Ebegan%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20his%20racist%20%E2%80%9Cbirther%E2%80%9D%20conspiracies%20about%20Obama.%20It%20is%20not%20a%20stretch%20to%20suggest%20many%20of%20his%20supporters%20would%20baulk%20at%20a%20ticket%20that%20wasn't%20entirely%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20a%20conservative%20woman%20might%20make%20sense%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20second%20category%2C%20the%20accepted%20wisdom%20is%20that%20Trump's%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fbiden-v-trump-winning-suburbia-is-key-to-clinching-the-presidency-in-2024-225248%5C%22%3Ewoman%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9D%20is%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20the%20signature%20achievement%20of%20his%20administration%3A%20the%20appointment%20of%20three%20conservative%20justices%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20which%20subsequently%20led%20to%20the%20overturning%20of%20Roe%20v%20Wade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Biden%20put%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.whitehouse.gov%2Fbriefing-room%2Fspeeches-remarks%2F2024%2F03%2F07%2Fremarks-of-president-joe-biden-state-of-the-union-address-as-prepared-for-delivery-2%2F%5C%22%3Erecently%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20candidates%20underestimate%20the%20political%20and%20electoral%20power%20of%20women%20at%20their%20peril.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20the%20leading%20women%20Republican%20VP%20candidates%20are%20Elise%20Stefanik%2C%20a%20congresswoman%20from%20New%20York%2C%20and%20Kristi%20Noem%2C%20the%20governor%20of%20South%20Dakota.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20both%20are%20considered%20leading%20candidates%20reveals%20the%20political%20calculations%20behind%20Trump's%20possible%20selection.%20While%20Trump%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftime.com%2F6335088%2Fdonald-trump-abortion-position-2024-election%2F%5C%22%3Eflip-flopped%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20abortion%20restrictions%20himself%2C%20both%20Stefanik%20and%20Noem%20have%20extremely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2022%2F07%2F03%2Fpolitics%2Fkristi-noem-south-dakota-abortion-trigger-ban%2Findex.html%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DSouth%2520Dakota%2520governor%2520defends%2520state%2527s%2Cbe%2520forced%2520to%2520give%2520birth%26amp%3Btext%3DSouth%2520Dakota%2520Republican%2520Gov.%2Ccases%2520involving%2520incest%2520or%2520rape.%5C%22%3Econservative%20positions%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20reproductive%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20given%20what%20we%20know%20about%20Trump's%20views%20on%20women%2C%20it%20seems%20likely%20his%20judgement%20would%20be%20almost%20entirely%20aesthetic.%20There%20is%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3