emergencies%20or%20scheduling%20changes.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20universal%20headache%3A%20Your%20phone%20rings%20after%20work%20hours%2C%20and%20it's%20your%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20don't%20know%20exactly%20what%20he%20or%20she%20wants%2C%20but%20it's%20probably%20not%20to%20wish%20you%20a%20good%20night%20or%20a%20happy%20weekend.%20More%20likely%20than%20not%2C%20an%20after-hours%20call%20means%20more%20work%20for%20you.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorking%20conditions%20have%20changed%20since%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20which%20put%20legions%20of%20workers%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcategory%2Fremote-work%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremote%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhybrid-work-bringing-women-back-to-the-labor-force-jobs-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehybrid%20schedules%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20of%20those%20flexible%20schedules%20and%20location%20policies%20remain%20in%20place%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20workers%20to%20establish%20a%20concrete%20end%20to%20their%20workday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20California%2C%20one%20Democratic%20lawmaker%20wants%20to%20solve%20that%20by%20codifying%20a%20worker's%20right%20to%20ignore%20communications%20from%20their%20boss%20after%20work%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20now%20find%20themselves%20always%20on%20and%20never%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20Assemblymember%20Matt%20Haney%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2024%2F03%2F30%2Fus%2Fright-to-disconnect-work-calls-california.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20New%20York%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BThe%20problem%20we%20have%20now%20is%20the%20gray%20area%2C%20where%20an%20employee%20is%20expected%20to%20respond%20all%20the%20time%20when%20on%20paper%20they%20work%20a%209-to-5%20job.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFiled%20in%20February%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fleginfo.legislature.ca.gov%2Ffaces%2Fbill